  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0dd2\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dba\u0ddd \u0db6\u0dab \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf \u0dc4\u0dcf\u0db8\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dd4 \u0dc0\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Lay people preach and monks plant",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Former Minister Wimal Weerawansa said that the country is currently moving towards a new birth and some people are trying to abort it.",
        "He said this on the occasion of establishing the Uttar Lanka Council.",
        "\"We are at a transformative moment. When going from one state to another. During surgery. At a time when a new birth is creating a new situation. During pregnancy.",
        "Some try to abort that new birth. Abort that new birth and continue to maintain the old birth. We are establishing the Uttar Lanka Council today not to be the representatives of the group that prevents that birth, but to give the necessary strength for the birth of a proud Sri Lanka that will grow in the womb.",
        "The politics that have existed so far in this era of transformation are going to the end. Conservative politics is dying out. Conventional thinkers cannot even think about this. This era of transformation is born by transferring the power of the state from the hands of the Durjanas to the hands of the Satjanas, and not in any other way.",
        "We were also in big coalitions. They think we are small parties. But when we finish the work we started, it is the people of this country who crush the big people and make the small people bigger.",
        "At this time lay people preach. Some monks cultivate. Doctors talk about fertilizers. The criminology graduate works as a development officer in a domain. Many such distortions can be shown. We need to get this country out of this distortion.",
        "If anyone thinks that Sri Lanka has been given to a few families for free, let a few families rule this country. For the Senanayakes, the Kothalawalas, the Bandaranayakes, the Rajapaksas, and so on for another family. The time when the throne of this country was handed over to those families is over. Rather than kings who came from families, it is the kings who came out of it that have done justice to Sri Lanka.\""
      ],
